@node "requirements" "Requirements"

 Launch Version 4+ requires the following external Files:

	Reqtools.library

	OS3.5+

 Launch WILL NOT work with less than OS3.5, It will run and you can configure it, but it won't be able to run anything as it uses features only available in the OS3.5+ Workbench.Library
@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"

Installation:

 Copy Launch into WBStartup, Thats it, Easy enough for you?

Usage:

 When you first run launch you should get a window open in the top left corner of workbench with 2 gadgets in it. Clicking on System will open a drop down menu with one entry in it. If you press 'a' when the menu is open an AppWindow will open and any files you drop onto it will be sorted alphabetically and added to the menu, Close the window when you have finished.

 To delete an entry open the menu and hilight the entry you wish to remove and press del, a requester will pop up asking if you really want to delete it and also give you the option of deleting the whole menu.

 You can rename any item in a menu by hilighting it and pressing e.

The Setup Menu:

  Add Menu (M) Adds a new menu ­ maximum of 32 menus.

  Swap Menu (W) Swaps the position of 2 menus.

  Rename Menu (N) Change the name of the menu.

  Add Item (I) Pops up a window with a cycle gadget to let you pick the menu to add files to. Just choose an option then drop files onto the window. Close it when your finished. the config is automatically saved to ENV:, to make it permanent use the save option.

  Restore (R) Reloads the config from ENVARC:

  Save (S) Perminently saves the config in ENVARC:

Hints & Tips:

 To easily access the menus click and hold the left mouse button on any
 gadget, drag the mouse off the gadget then let go.  This will have activated
 the window so the right mouse can now access the titlebar menus.
@endnode

